==English==

===Etymology===

From the {{L.}} ''[[malevolentia]]'', derived from ''[[malevolens|malēvolens]]'' ([[malevolent]]).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# [[hostile|Hostile]] attitude and feeling.
#: ''To show someone '''malevolence'''.''
#: ''He said it with '''malevolence'''.''
# [[ill-will|Ill-will]], [[malice]], [[spite]].

